<document>
    <properties>
        <title>in Servlet Container</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Deploying in Servlet Container">
          <span class='shortdesc'>Get Hippo CMS up and running in a Java <span class='index' id='servlet_container'>servlet container</span>.</span>

            <subsection name="Obtain the WAR package">
              <p>
                To deploy Hippo CMS in a servlet container, download the WAR package.
                <span class='expire_event'>release</span>Hippo ECM is still under development, 
                but you can already get a snapshot version:
              </p>
<source>
  <a href='http://repository.hippocms.org/maven2/org/hippoecm/hippo-ecm-quickstart-war/2.01.00.14160/hippo-ecm-quickstart-war-2.01.00.14160.war'>Quickstart WAR</a>
</source>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Deploying in Tomcat 6.0">
                <ol>
                    <li>Download <span class='index' id='tomcat_6.0'>Tomcat 6.0</span> from the <a href="http://tomcat.apache.org/download-60.cgi">Apache Tomcat</a> website.</li>
                    <li>Unpack the zip.</li>
                    <li>Download the <a href="http://repo1.maven.org/maven/geronimo-spec/jars/geronimo-spec-jta-1.0-M1.jar">geronimo-spec-jta</a> to pache-tomcat-6.0.16\lib</li>
                    <li>Copy the WAR from the link above to the webapps/ folder as cms.war</li>
                    <li>Start Tomcat.</li>
                    <li>Open your browser and surf to <a href="http://localhost:8080/cms/">http://localhost:8080/cms/</a>..</li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Deploying in Tomcat 5.5">
                <ol>
                    <li>Download <span class='index' id='tomcat_5.5'>Tomcat 5.5</span> from the <a href="http://tomcat.apache.org/download-55.cgi">Apache Tomcat</a> website</li>
                    <li>Unpack the zip</li>
                    <li>Download the <a href="http://repo1.maven.org/maven/geronimo-spec/jars/geronimo-spec-jta-1.0-M1.jar">geronimo-spec-jta</a> to pache-tomcat-6.0.16\lib</li>
                    <li>Copy the WAR from the link above to the webapps/ folder as cms.war</li>
                    <li>Start Tomcat.</li>
                    <li>Open your browser and surf to <a href="http://localhost:8080/cms/">http://localhost:8080/cms/</a>.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    Some users reported the following error on startup "Configuration file syntax error.: Premature end of file." This can be resolved by adding the following two jars to the Tomcat endorsed lib folder in common:
                </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><a href="http://repo1.maven.org/maven/xalan/jars/xalan-2.7.1.jar">xalan</a></li>
                        <li><a href="http://repo1.maven.org/maven/xalan/jars/serializer-2.7.1.jar">xalan serializer</a></li>
                    </ol>
            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
